The Food Standards Agency in Britain has issued a recall of over 350 food products due to the discovery of a cancer-causing dye, Sudan I, in a batch of chilli powder used in various items.
The agency is working with supermarkets to remove affected products and advises the public to return them for a refund.
The investigation involves multiple local authorities and has led to the recall of 474 items.
The European Union is also on alert, with 12 other countries notified.
China has banned imports of any foods containing Sudan I, emphasizing the seriousness of the situation.
